</p>

<h3>Arrogya</h3>
<p>
<a class="resource" href="http://www.aarogya.com/SupportGroup/index.asp">http://www.aarogya.com/SupportGroup/index.asp</a><br />
<strong><em>Description</em></strong><br />
This Web site has a link to support groups for persons with disabilities, epilepsy, AIDS, cancer, schizophrenia and heart ailments.
</p>

<h3>Schools for the Blind and Vocational Training Centers</h3>
<p>
<a class="resource" href="http://www.webelmediatronics.in/brlads/govt_maharashtra.htm">http://www.webelmediatronics.in/brlads/govt_maharashtra.htm</a>
</p>

<h3>Soulmate.org.IN</h3>
<p>
<a class="resource" href="http://www.soulmate.org.in/">http://www.soulmate.org.in/</a><br />
The project <strong>Soulmate.org.in</strong> is an automated, web-based matchmaking system for differently-abled persons 
and is set up and owned by <strong>Rotary Club of Bombay Pier (RCBP)</strong>, Mumbai, India.
</p>

<h3>Karmayog</h3>
<p>
<a class="resource" href="http://www.karmayog.org/">http://www.karmayog.org/</a><br />
Presents contact information of NGOs working in India in the areas of animal welfare, art and culture, disabilities, environment, science, human rights, social justice, medicine, education and vocational guidance. Information on nonprofits working for women's rights, Mahila Mandals, support groups for disabilities, sex abuse, drug and alcohol abuse, as well as organizations catering to senior citizens is also available. In addition the 
Web site also gives information on acts, laws and schemes passed by Indian Government.
</p>

<h3>Disability India</h3>
<p>
<a class="resource" href="http://www.disabilityindia.org/">http://www.disabilityindia.org/</a><br />
Hosted by the Society for Child Development, Disability India Network is a comprehensive site for information related to disability in India. The 
Web site has contact information of manufacturers and suppliers of aids and 
appliances for persons with hearing impairments, visual impairments, and 
physical impairments. Acts pertaining to disability such as the Person&#8217;s with 
Disabilities Act, the National Trust Act, the RCI Act and the Mental Health Act can be downloaded. Articles on issues around inclusion and other issues pertaining to special education in India can be downloaded from the Disability India Journal as well as from their online library. The 
Web site also provides information on government services, facilities and benefits, financial assistance and registration of societies. Also available are a discussion forum and an organization search in different states in India.
</p>

